I did compile it. The problem is not `self.identifier_preparer.quote_identifier`. In _pyhive_, the method [get_table_names()](https://github.com/dropbox/PyHive/blob/44717f7b5f1b09d615a0e8d14c9c0ae15404c576/pyhive/sqlalchemy_hive.py#L303), they must have taken the second item of each tuple, but they took the first item which is the database name. An example of the original result is here: 
`[(u'default', u'tb', False), (u'default', u'tb2', False), (u'default', u'tb3', False)]
` 
I reported this [issue](https://github.com/dropbox/PyHive/issues/150) to Pyhive.

I experienced the same behaviour except I used Spark Temp Tables and with them the returned tuples were like `(u'', u'tablename', True)` where the first item is the schema/database name, the second is the name of the table and the third is for deciding if the table is temporary or not. That's why I was getting back empty strings instead of table names so my conclusion is the same. Thanks for creating a Pyhive issue @rezabaktash.
